winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are great choices for Fish. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. You could try Tiamo Pinot Grigio. Reviewers quite like it with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 11 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Tiamo Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: Light straw yellow color. Fresh and rich fruity aromas of apple and pear with a hint of citrus fruit that fade into the floral bouquet. Fresh and fruity, very clean and crisp.Tiamo Pinot Grigio pairs well with a wide array of lighter cuisine, especially fish/shellfish, poultry, pastas in cream sauce and softer cheeses. It's also an ideal aperitif.

instructions: In a saucepan, mix clam juice and carrots.Simmer 'til carrots are crunchy-tender.Meanwhile in a large saucepan, fry onions in oil 'til transparent.Add the seasonings and optional salt - and fry another 4 minutes.Stir the clam juice and carrots into the onions and simmer 5 minutes.Add the fish and cilantro and simmer 8-10 minutes or 'til fish is of desired doneness.Add water if needed and adjust seasonings.Garnish with cilantro leaves or parsley and serve.Salsa and hot sauce can be present on the table.

steps.step: In a saucepan, mix clam juice and carrots.Simmer 'til carrots are crunchy-tender.Meanwhile in a large saucepan, fry onions in oil 'til transparent.
Add the seasonings and optional salt - and fry another 4 minutes.Stir the clam juice and carrots into the onions and simmer 5 minutes.
Add the fish and cilantro and simmer 8-10 minutes or 'til fish is of desired doneness.
Add water if needed and adjust seasonings.
Garnish with cilantro leaves or parsley and serve.Salsa and hot sauce can be present on the table.
